<subSubSection id="40F165701277FFC2FF62FBC3FEC66F6E" pageId="18" pageNumber="675" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="085436FB1277FFC2FF62FBC3FEC66F6E" blockId="18.[151,1127,1049,1586]" pageId="18" pageNumber="675">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE91277FFC2FF62FBC3FEA16E4E" bold="true" box="[151,268,1049,1073]" pageId="18" pageNumber="675">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium-sized (6.0– 
<quantity id="CF139B1E1277FFC2FE1FFBC0FD936E4D" box="[490,574,1050,1074]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="18" pageNumber="675" unit="mm" value="6.7">6.7 mm</quantity>
), slightly prognathous, stout, cuneiform, rather convex, lustrous (
<figureCitation id="90D02A7E1277FFC2FEC7FBE0FED86E2D" box="[306,373,1082,1106]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="4.[825,862,1206,1225]" captionTargetBox="[151,1128,220,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[151,1126,219,1542]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–8. Agrilaxia, dorsal aspect. 1 – Agrilaxia cacao sp. nov., holo- type ♀, 7.2 mm; 2 – A. bongrandi Cobos, 1972, J (Route de Cacao), 6.0 mm; 3 – A.claudei Cobos, 1972, ♀ (Bélizon), 8.0 mm; 4 – A. tristis Cobos, 1972, ♀ (Saul), 7.2 mm; 5 – A. elegans sp. nov., holotype J, 7.8 mm; 6 – A. cordicollis sp. nov., holotype J, 6.5 mm; 7 – A. glabra sp. nov., holotype ♀, 6.0 mm; 8 – A. sulcifrons sp. nov., holotype J, 6.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740764/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="675">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); elytra black with rather strong green or violet tinge, narrow sutural and transverse, basal stripes golden green or golden orange; pronotum golden-orange or golden green, with two wide, black, longitudinal spots reaching both anterior and posterior margins, golden stripe between them very narrow, somewhat widened anteriorly; head black with green or bronze tinge; vertex, antennae and legs bronze; ventral surface purple or bright golden-red, posterior half of anal ventrite darkened, metepisterna black with blue lustre; entire body asetose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
